  "A pattern or relationship in nature that has been observed repeatedly": "",
  "A guess about what might happen during a scientific experiment": "",
  "A rule that scientists must follow when conducting any experiment": "",
  "A scientific law describes what happens — a consistent pattern or relationship observed in nature. For example, the law of gravity describes that objects always fall toward Earth, but it does not explain why.": "",
  "What does a scientific theory explain?": "",
  "Only what happens during a natural event, not why it happens": "",
  "Why a natural phenomenon occurs, supported by extensive evidence": "",
  "A personal opinion about how nature works without any evidence": "",
  "A prediction about a future event that has not yet been tested": "",
  "A scientific theory explains why something happens in nature. It is supported by a large body of evidence from many experiments and observations. For example, the theory of gravity explains why objects attract each other.": "",
