  "Yes, all theories eventually become laws with enough evidence": "",
  "No, theories and laws are different types of scientific knowledge": "",
  "Yes, but only after 100 years of continuous testing by scientists": "",
  "No, because theories are just guesses that are never proven right": "",
  "Theories do not become laws. They serve different purposes: laws describe what happens (patterns), while theories explain why things happen. Both are well-supported by evidence but answer different questions.": "",
