  "What is a scientific law?": "",
  "A statement that describes a consistent, observable pattern in nature based on evidence": "",
  "A detailed explanation of the underlying mechanism that causes events in nature": "",
  "A rule that all scientists must follow when they conduct experiments in a lab": "",
  "A prediction made by a scientist before any data is collected or analyzed": "",
  "A scientific law is a concise statement describing a pattern or relationship consistently observed in nature. Laws are based on extensive evidence and can often be expressed as mathematical equations.": "",
  "What is a scientific theory?": "",
  "A well-supported explanation of why a natural phenomenon occurs based on evidence": "",
  "A brief statement that describes what always happens under certain conditions": "",
  "An untested guess about how the natural world might work in the future": "",
  "A personal opinion about science that requires no experimental evidence": "",
  "A scientific theory is a comprehensive explanation of why a natural phenomenon occurs, supported by a large body of evidence from multiple experiments and observations. Examples include the theory of evolution and atomic theory.": "",
  "What does 'hypothesis' mean compared to a theory?": "",
