  "A proven fact that has much more evidence supporting it than a theory": "",
  "A final conclusion that replaces a theory after an experiment is completed": "",
  "A mathematical equation describing a pattern observed repeatedly in nature": "",
  "A hypothesis is a testable prediction based on limited observations. A theory is supported by extensive evidence from many experiments. A hypothesis may eventually contribute to building or refining a theory.": "",
  "What does 'evidence' mean in science?": "",
  "Data and observations that support or contradict a scientific claim": "",
  "A personal feeling or belief about how the natural world operates": "",
  "The equipment and materials used to conduct a scientific experiment": "",
  "The written instructions for performing a laboratory procedure step": "",
  "Evidence consists of data and observations collected through experiments or studies that either support or contradict a scientific claim. Both laws and theories must be supported by strong evidence.": "",
