  "An observation that has been confirmed repeatedly and is accepted as true": "",
  "A prediction about what will happen in a future experiment or observation": "",
  "A personal opinion shared by the majority of scientists in the community": "",
  "An explanation of why something happens that may or may not have support": "",
  "A scientific fact is an observation or measurement that has been confirmed repeatedly and is accepted as true. For example, 'water boils at 100°C at sea level' is a fact.": "",
