  "Both the law and the theory describe the same thing using different words": "",
  "The law is a guess; the theory is a fact that has been confirmed by testing": "",
  "The law describes the pattern (objects at rest stay at rest unless a force acts on them). The theory explains why (objects have inertia — a property that resists changes in motion). Law = what, Theory = why.": "",
  "A scientist discovers new evidence that contradicts an accepted theory. What should happen?": "",
